		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div></div><blockquote dir="ltr"><p><em>Please refrain from posting personal attacks and make some constructive criticism, I'd appreciate some real input here instead of the standard:<br><br>I don't think it should be no for no other reason then casters shouldn't have something melee gets.</em></p></blockquote><p>No.</p><p>Casters are masters of the mind and magical arts. They weave the fabric of magic (mana) into physical manifestations. In fact many books/hero's of magic are physical cripples. Physical prowess and use of the physical body is the last thing on a casters mind, except using the legs to get from A to B (and in some cases like wizards, even thats lessened !).</p><p>If you want extra skills, sure go for it, but not as endurance based skills, you have as much right to an endurance disc as a monk does to cast a 10K fireball and then teleport out. Ask for them as spells, as AA's, as innate abilities of the class.</p>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=597" target="_blank">Azathool</a> Guild Leader of &lt<a href="http://www.nwguild.com" target="_blank">Nightwatcher</a>&gt <a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/view_profile?user.id=23916" target="_blank">Monk Community Correspondent</a> <br><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1024677" target="_blank">Cleric</a> & <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4174" target="_blank">Shaman</a>
							</div>
								
