			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>I dont see the similiarity between the roogues inablity to play a group encounter before disc&nbsp;and a wizards inability to play a group encounter now.&nbsp; I think your reaching from that perspective.&nbsp; Im not arguing the situation isnt close to parity now.&nbsp; Because thats not what was in your post.&nbsp; You said there is a similiarity between the position wizards are in NOW regarding the ability to play group encounters and the situation rogues were in THEN.&nbsp; And if thats not what you said you should clarify or backpedal cause its a pretty weak position if you ask me.</P>
<P>One of the biggest issues is wizards still have most of the tools they had THEN.&nbsp; And when you compared a wizards ability to play things like overpulls to a rogue without only 1 disc every 20 minutes ability to play things like overpulls it was night and day.&nbsp; The rogue had very little in the way of doing things different just cause 3 mobs were in camp after 12 seconds was up.&nbsp; It was a very flat grouping existance.&nbsp; </P>
<P>When the disc changes went in it was obvious we had moved a step closer to parity in FUN FACTOR.&nbsp; However your trying to claim some how wizards have gotten the short end of the stick and have had their ability to play group situations eroded over the years.</P>
<P>Gl&nbsp; with that but claiming there is some sort of parity between a wizard&nbsp;NOW in groups and a melee THEN before disc in groups doesnt convince me... personally.</P>
<P>edit:</P>
<P>and to the thief ive said forever hi end rogues in a magical universe would be spell casting hybrids!&nbsp; Rogues through history have shown that the rogue "idea" will adapt the technology of their sorroundings.&nbsp; Rogues on the web adapt CS ideas to roguely ends.&nbsp; Rogues in the woods adapt woodsmen technology to their use.&nbsp; Rogues in medieval europe reflected their culture.&nbsp; Rogues in asia adapted the knowledge of that particular area.&nbsp; Where ever you go a rogue is defined by bastardizing whats available for their nefarious ends.&nbsp; So the best rogues in a spell casting world would be spell casters..</P><p>Message Edited by Qutsemnie on <span class=date_text>04-20-2006</span> <span class=time_text>11:26 AM</span>	
