			<div></div><div><span><br><blockquote><hr>Azathool wrote:<br><blockquote dir="ltr"><p><em>Please refrain from posting personal attacks and make some constructive criticism, I'd appreciate some real input here instead of the standard:<br><br>I don't think it should be no for no other reason then casters shouldn't have something melee gets.</em></p></blockquote><p>No.</p><p>Casters are masters of the mind and magical arts. They weave the fabric of magic (mana) into physical manifestations. In fact many books/hero's of magic are physical cripples. Physical prowess and use of the physical body is the last thing on a casters mind, except using the legs to get from A to B (and in some cases like wizards, even thats lessened !).</p><p>If you want extra skills, sure go for it, but not as endurance based skills, you have as much right to an endurance disc as a <u>monk does to cast a 10K fireball</u> and then teleport out. Ask for them as spells, as AA's, as innate abilities of the class.</p><br><hr></blockquote>a fireball sounds wicked but i think this would be cooler:<br><br><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shoryuken" target="_blank">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shoryuken</a><br><br><br></span><b>Shoryuken</b>, properly pronounced (SHOR-REE-YOO-KEN), is roughly the Japanese translation meaning "Rising Dragon Fist" <i>("Sho"=Rising, "Ryu"=Dragon, "Ken"=Fist or Punch)</i>. It an attack developed by Goutetsu the creator of the martial art <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ansatsuken" title="Ansatsuken" target="_blank">Ansatsuken</a> <i>(or Shotokan)</i>.
It is an aerial punch that spirals in mid-air and is very devastating.
In the Goutetsu style of Ansatsuken, the Shouryuuken was meant to kill
anyone in one stroke. In Gouken's school, the Shouryuuken was meant to
bring the opponent closer to defeat, even without the Shouryuuken's
"initial killing touch"<br><br><br>PS:&nbsp; casters can always melee while on or off a horse and it doesn't affect their mana regen while melee has to deal with poor regen while fighting and pulling, id say that's hardly fair<br></div><p>Message Edited by Nedrom on <span class=date_text>04-20-2006</span> <span class=time_text>02:25 PM</span>
