		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<div><p>Endurance based discs for casters.... eh, no thanks.  IMO the current endurance system is broke as is, it does nothing to limit melees minus warriors and that's on less frequency than a wizzy and his mana.  It should be a limiting device or why else have a endurance system at all?</p><p>If you want &quot;discs&quot; for casters then they should be done via AA.   They shouldn't have such steep costs for relatively low performance like PD. However, I don't think &quot;discs&quot; of any sorts is the key to fixing wizards as a class, it needs to be done thru equipment, new foci (i.e. crit modifier), less huge random effects (i.e. 1-65%), and increasing % on old foci (spellhaste, mana pres).  Also, another step to fixing the wizard class is the agro, w/o a much more effective system of not getting agro, wizards, as a class, are screwed.  Mana regen or consumption also needs to be changed simply cause running oom and staying oom doesn't help the cause. </p><p>The bottom line is that wizards, should maybe at some point get some issues addressed, I really don't care how. I've been saying this since GoD, and I still see this gap b/w melees and wizards, and very little effort to close that gap.</p></div>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Sacora Syv -- Wizard of Assent
							</div>
								
